node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Business Equity on August 12, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets averaged a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo shared by Business Equity on August 12, 2021 tagging @gritcapital. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter managed millions of dollars in investor money for nearly a decade and one of the funds ran with ~$30MM in assets averaged a 13% return for 7 years And let me tell you, there are some important lessons that learned.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 1.Risk is fine in moderation. It's alright to make some risky investments here and there, but it shouldn't be a high % of your portfolio. 20% of my portfolio is dedicated to higher-risk investments.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve och-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 2. The best deals are private. Even though there are tons of great options to invest in with the open stock market investing in private deals gives you access to more 10x and 100x opportunities.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 3. Big gains are nice, but consistent gains are key. Even though winningit oig on some call options will give me you a nice screenshot, what really matters is your compound annual growth rate over 10, 20, or 30 years. don't like options.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says '-DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 4. Day trading is bad. This should be self-explanatory, but if Warren Buffet, the greatest investor of all time isn't making any trades, neither am I.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 5. Most people are better with ETF's. When it comes down to picking individual stocks, most people (even hedge funds) will not outperform basic EFTs like vOO and SPY over 30 years. If you you can't beat them, join them.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 12, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter Now that I'm no longer managing other people's money, I'm your local financial meme dealer. make content that is both educating and entertaining while writing some newsletters every week. The best part? The content and one of my newsletters are free if you follow me.'.

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'BusinessEquity C SHAQUILLE O'NEAL ONCE SAID lheard Jeff Bezos say one time that he makes his investments based on if it's going to change people's lives. Once started doing that strategy, think probably quadrupled what I'm worth.'.

node.text:
The idea is to invest in things that are actually changing peoples lives...those things are much more likely to stay around longer and actually make money.

For example, investing into Amazon 2 decades ago could have brought a HUGE return on investment, and its a company that actually makes peoples lives easier.

Follow us @businessequity

What are your thoughts on this?

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
Breaking generational cycles isn't for the weak.

This is what we mean when we say don't listen to your friends, family and neighbors. We're not saying to never speak to them again, but you have a goal and if you're serious about reaching that goal you're going to have to block out the noise

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
We all have the same amount of time in our days.

If you work a 9-5 it's likely that you have 2 days off a week. If you hate your current job don't slack off on the weekend. You have 48 hours (at the minimum for the entire week) to make a change.

The opportunites are endless...you can start a side hustle from basically anything. 

Follow us @businessequity
